- **People and Roles:** Virgin Mary, Joseph of Arimathea, Nicodemus, grieving women
- **Gestures and Poses:** Mourning, supporting, kneeling
- **Objects and Symbols:** Shroud, body of Christ, skull, landscape
- **Architecture and Landscape:** Rolling hills, distant castles, natural elements
- **Emotions and Psychology:** Grief, reverence, despair
- **Narrative Themes:** Entombment of Christ, biblical sacrifice, mourning of loss